Introduction

This Rmarkdown file has been made to visualize the movement of dengue incidences imported to Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh city. We will use 3 datasets: incidence_df_clean stored in DART share folder, shape file level 1 dataset stored in DART github repository and the census 2019 dataset.

I. Impoprt all datasets

  • First, we import incidence dataset that has been cleaned and stored in DART share folder
incidence_df <- readRDS("/Volumes/special$/DART/incidence_data_cleaning/incidence_df_clean.rds")
incidence_df %<>%
  mutate(
    across(
      c(reported_unit_province, province),
      .fns = ~ recode(.x,
        "bà rịa-v.tàu" = "bà rịa - vũng tàu",
        "tp. h.c.m" = "hồ chí minh",
        "tt- huế" = "thừa thiên huế"
      )
    )
  )
  • Count the number of dengue incidences were reported at HCM and Hanoi by province.
tmp <- incidence_df %>%
  select("id", "province", "reported_unit_province") %>%
  filter(reported_unit_province == "hồ chí minh" | reported_unit_province == "hà nội") %>%
  group_by(province, reported_unit_province) %>%
  summarise(count = n()) %>%
  ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'province'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
  • Second, we import shape file dataset level 1
shape <- readRDS("~/OneDrive - Oxford University Clinical Research Unit/DARTgit/Dengue/disease_incidence/gadm41_VNM_1_pk.rds") %>%
  terra::unwrap() %>%
  st_as_sf()
  • Then we will convert all the province names into lower case, so that it can be easily matched with the incidence data. For this task, we will only select the lower cased names and the polygon geometry.
shape %<>% mutate(NAME_1 = tolower(NAME_1)) %>%
  select(4) %>%
  mutate_at("NAME_1", ~ str_replace_all(.x, "hòa", "hoà"))
  • And get the central point coordinates of each province
shape1 <- st_centroid(shape)
## Warning in st_centroid.sf(shape): st_centroid assumes attributes are constant
## over geometries of x
shape2 <- as.data.frame(shape1 %>% bind_cols(st_coordinates(shape1$geometry))) %>%
  select("NAME_1", "Y", "X") %>%
  rename(lat = Y, lon = X)
  • Third, we import the census 2019 data and clean some values to match with our incidence data
census <- readRDS("~/OneDrive - Oxford University Clinical Research Unit/DART/vietnam_pop/census2019.rds") %>%
  group_by(province) %>%
  summarise(n = sum(n)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(province = str_to_lower(province)) %>%
  mutate(province = str_replace_all(province, "thành phố ", "")) %>%
  mutate(province = str_replace_all(province, "tỉnh ", "")) %>%
  mutate(
    province = str_replace_all(province, "đăk lăk", "đắk lắk"),
    province = str_replace_all(province, "đăk nông", "đắk nông"),
    province = str_replace_all(province, "thanh hoá", "thanh hóa")
  )

# In the census dataset, Vinh Long province was not included. We used information from https://www.gso.gov.vn/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Ket-qua-toan-bo-Tong-dieu-tra-dan-so-va-nha-o-2019.pdf which provide population of Vinh Long province 2019 is 1022791

census[63, "province"] <- "vĩnh long"
census[63, "n"] <- as.numeric("1022791")

II. Visualiation

Movement of imported cases to HCM

hcm <- tmp %>%
  filter(reported_unit_province == "hồ chí minh") %>%
  left_join(shape2, by = c("province" = "NAME_1")) %>%
  rename(other_lat = lat, other_lon = lon) %>%
  left_join(shape2, c("reported_unit_province" = "NAME_1")) %>%
  rename(hcm_lat = lat, hcm_lon = lon) %>%
  filter(!province == "hồ chí minh") %>%
  left_join(census, c("province" = "province")) %>%
  mutate(proportion = log(count / n * 10^6))

hcm <- as.data.frame(hcm)
df <- osrmTable(
  src = hcm[1, c("hcm_lon", "hcm_lat")],
  dst = hcm[, c("other_lon", "other_lat")]
)

hcm <- hcm %>%
  mutate(duration = as.vector(df$durations)) %>%
  mutate(duration = if_else(duration >= 700, 120, duration)) %>%
  mutate(color = ifelse(duration == 120, "red", "black"))
p1 <- ggplot(hcm, aes(duration, proportion, color = color)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  labs(x = "Duration (minutes)", y = "Log transform number of imported cases to HCM") +
  scale_color_identity(labels = c("prvovinces with duration < 700 minutes", "prvovinces with duration > 700 minutes"), guide = "legend")+
  labs( color = "")+
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",
        legend.direction = "vertical")

p2 <- ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = shape) +
  theme(
    panel.grid = element_blank(),
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
    axis.text.x = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),
    axis.text.y = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks.y = element_blank()
  ) +
  geom_point(
    data = hcm,
    aes(x = hcm_lon, y = hcm_lat, size = proportion, color = proportion)
  ) +
  geom_point(
    data = hcm,
    aes(x = other_lon, y = other_lat, color = proportion)
  ) +
  scale_color_viridis_c(labels = function(x) format(x, scientific = FALSE)) +
  geom_curve(
    data = hcm,
    aes(
      x = hcm_lon, y = hcm_lat,
      xend = other_lon, yend = other_lat,
      color = proportion
    ),
    alpha = 0.8,
    curvature = 0.2
  ) +
  labs(x = "", y = "", color = "") +
  guides(size = "none")

p1+p2

Movement of imported cases to Hanoi

hn <- tmp %>%
  filter(reported_unit_province == "hà nội") %>%
  left_join(shape2, by = c("province" = "NAME_1")) %>%
  rename(other_lat = lat, other_lon = lon) %>%
  left_join(shape2, c("reported_unit_province" = "NAME_1")) %>%
  rename(hn_lat = lat, hn_lon = lon) %>%
  filter(!province == "hà nội") %>%
  left_join(census, c("province" = "province")) %>%
  mutate(proportion = log(count / n * 10^6))

hn <- as.data.frame(hn)
df <- osrmTable(
  src = hn[1, c("hn_lon", "hn_lat")],
  dst = hn[, c("other_lon", "other_lat")]

hn <- hn %>%
  mutate(duration = as.vector(df$durations)) %>%
  mutate(duration = if_else(duration >= 700, 120, duration)) %>%
  mutate(color = ifelse(duration == 120, "red", "black"))

p1 <- ggplot(hn, aes(duration, proportion, color = color)) +
